Reasoning: The paper deals with the computational complexity of comparison-based algorithms for fundamental problems such as Minimum, Selection, Sorting, and Heap Construction. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new concept called "fragile complexity" and provides upper and lower bounds on it, which indicates that the paper may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from Information Theory (cs.IT) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) to prove its results. Finally, the paper discusses the possibility of achieving lower fragile complexity with randomization, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
